{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"Design challenge resolved (handoff session c18e-6b87-cde8-4148): the outbound differ compared in vendor shape, so its comparison helpers had no ADR 0035 §(d)-legal home (port extension was BLOCKED by plan review on 97f2/change 920; keeping them in core kept the core vendor-shaped). Resolution: the canonical-comparison principle — core compares only canonical shapes; the outbound differ canonicalizes the fetched snapshot via InboundMapper.map_remote_to_local (parity with inbound_differ.py:159) and builds vendor payloads only via the injected OutboundMapper at emission. Remediation decomposed into 5 open children: 97f2 re-scoped to the scalar port surface (project/query_project/assert_env_ready/neutral assignee error); 625b canonical field diff (+ADR §(d) amendment); eefd canonical link diff; aff0 SupportsAbsenceProbe (inbound_probe REST mechanics -> adapters/jira/probe.py, a residual missed by the original AC3 inventory); 21ca rich-text/comment-limit lazy-key literals behind FieldSanitizer/InboundMapper. Follow-up 556a (relocate inbound_fields.py) filed discovered_from, out of epic scope. Gerrit change 920 to be abandoned; its scalar subset is cherry-pickable from worktree impl-4af8-differ-di."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784820377092638001,"uuid":"665a3991-e130-4ffc-9051-96ba5f8e1e4e"}